definitions.definition: A masculine pronoun; he as a grammatical object.

subdefinitions.definition: With dative effect or as an indirect object.
With accusative effect or as a direct object.

definitions.definition: As a grammatical subject or object when joined with a conjunction.
examples: Now him and Bernie are best friends.
Released a [statement] warning that him and 25,000 troops were going to stage a coup.

definitions.definition: With nominative effect: he , especially as a predicate after be , or following a preposition.
A person of elevated skill at a sport , game , or other activity .
examples: Stop trying that, you're not him bro.

main_definition: A masculine pronoun; he as a grammatical object.
secondary_definitions: ( colloquial ) As a grammatical subject or object when joined with a conjunction.
( now rare ) Used reflexively : (to) himself . [from 9th c.]
With nominative effect: he , especially as a predicate after be , or following a preposition. [from 15th c.]
( slang ) A person of elevated skill at a sport , game , or other activity .
